properties.name: Ark fish restaurant
properties.description: Posted by Jonbray Posh fish \'n\' chips in civilised surroundings. Excellent food, but you can\'t reserve a table so be sure to turn up nice and early at the weekend!

properties.name: Clacton-on-Sea
properties.description: Posted by JonbrayNice place for a day out at the beach. Watch out for a dog called Asbo!

properties.name: Fishers Green
properties.description: Posted by JonbrayA great place to walk on a balmy summer\'s day. The bird life here is always entertaining and the paths around the lakes and waterways are flat and true enough to take the family out for a gentle bike ride. Beautiful countryside just minutes outside the captial...

properties.name: Hainault Forest Country Park
properties.description: Posted by Jonbray  Petting zoo and café - great place to let the kids off the leash for a few hours or to have a picnic. Can\'t vouch for the food in the café but the farm/zoo is great...

properties.name: High Beech
properties.description: Posted by JonbrayExcellent starting point for walks and cycle rides in Epping Forest. Don\'t bother with the café next to the pub or the pub itself for food - visit the humble tea hut in the car park, which stocks brilliant cakes and serves a nice cup of tea!

properties.name: Woods fish 'n' chips
properties.description: Posted by Jonbray One of the best local fish \'n\' chips places I know anywhere in London. A tad expensive but the batter is always crispy and the portions generous. Always busy on a Friday night!
